text: I don't bash modern digital gaming. I know it is very quasi-realistic. I understand why people dig it. The newer the better. Right? I don't know about that. Can a game be so serious and realistic to the point where simple, stupid fun is lost? I remember when pinball was digital fun and laughs. We had arcades 40+ years ago. We had Centipede, Pac Man, Donkey Kong, Ice Hockey and so on. Atari offered all that to our living rooms. We didn't have to go out anywhere to have fun with family and friends -- we did anyway. I guess young people today in 2025 will look back on 2025 as being the good ol' days when they are 60+ years older. The old always remember the good ol' days. The young will catch up.
